name: Claudia Jessie
summary: Claudia Jessie, who plays Eloise in the popular Netflix series "Bridgerton," has been generating headlines with her recent comments about her character's future. In an interview with Vanity Fair, she hinted at Eloise's "hurt" reaction to the potential romance between Colin and Penelope. Meanwhile, in an appearance on Teen Vogue, Jessie revealed that she wore the same suit twice during the show's Season 3 press tour. In another interview with Yahoo News Canada, she discussed the possibility of a queer storyline for Eloise, stating that "you can experiment more" with her character. This discussion was further fueled by comments from Business Insider and Capital, who reported on Jessie's belief that there is "room" for Eloise to have a queer romance. In an interview with ELLE UK, Jessie and co-star Luke Newton shared behind-the-scenes secrets from filming the show. Additionally, The Telegraph featured an article about Jessie's experiences as a working-class actress, highlighting the challenges she faced early in her career. summary: The highly-anticipated adaptation of Colleen Hoover's best-selling novel "It Ends with Us" has finally unveiled its first trailer. Starring Blake Lively as Lily Bloom, the trailer depicts a heart-wrenching romance filled with love, loss, and trauma. The adaptation has garnered significant attention from avid readers, particularly those on the social media platform BookTok. The trailer showcases Lively's chemistry with Justin Baldoni, who plays Ryle Kincaid, as their characters navigate a whirlwind romance amidst the complexities of past relationships and lingering wounds. The trailer features a haunting rendition of Taylor Swift's song "Carolina," adding an emotional depth to the preview. With its release date set, excitement is building for the film's debut, offering fans of the book a captivating adaptation of the beloved story.

summary: Australian soccer has been rocked by a match-fixing scandal involving the captain of Macarthur FC, Ulises Dávila. Police have arrested Dávila and two other Macarthur players after a pre-dawn raid, charging them with betting-related corruption. The arrests come after a long-running investigation by the NSW Police, who allege that the players were involved in a scheme to fix the outcome of A-League matches. The news has sent shockwaves through the Australian soccer community, with Macarthur FC expressing surprise and disappointment at the allegations. The A-League has also suspended the three players pending the outcome of the investigation.

name: Megalopolis
summary: Francis Ford Coppola's long-awaited film "Megalopolis" has received mixed reactions. Critics describe it as "totally nuts" (Vulture), with reviewers questioning Coppola's filmmaking abilities (The Guardian). The film, a "passion project gone horribly wrong" (Vanity Fair), is criticized for being farcical despite its tragic intentions (Toronto Star). Some find its urban sprawl captivating (The New Yorker), while others report boos and cheers at its Cannes premiere (World of Reel). Amidst the controversy, allegations emerge of Coppola's inappropriate behavior on set, including attempted kissing of extras and frequent cannabis use (Exclaim!). Despite the negative reception, the film will receive a global IMAX release (Hollywood Reporter).
